# Eoqrupics - A Photography Portfolio Website

Eoqrupics is a photography portfolio website designed to showcase my work as a photographer while incorporating my skills in web design. The project aims to create an aesthetically pleasing and user-friendly platform for displaying my portfolio and attracting potential clients.

## Motivation

As a photographer and web designer, I wanted to merge my two passions and create a portfolio that not only highlights my photography skills but also showcases my ability to design and develop interactive web experiences. This project serves as a platform for me to demonstrate my creativity and technical abilities while providing a professional showcase of my work.

## Technologies Used

- HTML
- CSS
- JavaScript
- Figma (for design)

## Features and Challenges

### Features Implemented
- Dynamically generated navigation sidebar using JavaScript to ensure consistency across multiple pages.
- Smooth page transitions with swipe-like animations for enhanced user experience.
- Translation feature allowing users to switch between English and Icelandic languages for all text content.
- Full-screen image viewing functionality with seamless navigation back to the portfolio.
- Responsive design optimized for various screen sizes, including mobile devices.

### Challenges Overcome
- Implementing dynamic navigation required careful consideration of DOM manipulation and event handling to ensure seamless integration across pages.
- Creating smooth page transitions involved experimenting with CSS animations and JavaScript timing functions to achieve the desired effect.
- Integrating translation functionality required utilizing JavaScript to ensure what page needed their text changed and pulling the different text from JSON files.

## Installation and Usage

1. Clone the repository: `git clone https://github.com/GuiRoque04/GuiRoque04.github.io.git`
2. Navigate to the project directory: `cd eoqrupics`
3. Open `index.html` in your web browser to access the portfolio.
4. Explore the various sections and features of the website to view the photography portfolio and experience the interactive elements.

or simply search www.eoqrupics.com


## Future Improvements

- Enhance accessibility features to ensure the website is usable by individuals with disabilities.
- Continuously optimize performance and user experience based on feedback and emerging technologies.

## Future Improvements outside of a static website

- Introduce dynamic forms clients can fill out, and reach out from.
- Introduce dynamic content management system (CMS) capabilities for easy updating and management of the portfolio.
